This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on dialect identification in Arabic broadcast speech, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of phonetic, lexical, and acoustic features also suggests that this paper could fall under the sub-categories of speech processing (cs.SD) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms such as Support Vector Machines (SVM) suggests that this paper could also fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
